    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've written:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: `next/geo` Utility Module\n\n### What's being added\nA new public entry point `next/geo` with four exports:\n- **`geolocation(request)`** — extracts `{ country, region, city, latitude, longitude }` from request headers (`x-vercel-ip-*` primary, `cf-ipcountry` Cloudflare fallback)\n- **`countryName(code, locale?)`** — ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 → display name via `Intl.DisplayNames`\n- **`isInRegion(geo, regionCodes)`** — checks if `geo.country` is in a list of codes\n- **`haversineDistance(from, to)`** — great-circle distance in km\n\n### Files to create (5 new, 1 edited — nothing existing changes)\n| | Path |\n|---|---|\n| Create | `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.ts` |\n| Create | `packages/next/src/api/geo.ts` |\n| Create | `packages/next/geo.js` |\n| Create | `packages/next/geo.d.ts` |\n| Create | `test/unit/geo.test.ts` |\n| Edit | `packages/next/package.json` — add `\"geo.js\"` and `\"geo.d.ts\"` to `\"files\"` |\n\n### Why no build system changes\nThe existing `api_esm` task in `taskfile.js` already globs `src/api/**/*.+(js|mts|ts|tsx)` — adding `src/api/geo.ts` is enough for it to compile automatically.\n\n### Model\nThe implementation mirrors the `userAgent` / `userAgentFromString` pattern in `spec-extension/user-agent.ts` — a pure, stateless function taking `{ headers: Headers }`, zero dependencies.",
